Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.16,0:03:07.08,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\an6\fad(2000,0)\blur0.6\pos(1220,109)}The Warbling Seashell
Dialogue: 5,0:03:31.97,0:03:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, are you collecting seashells too?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:36.95,0:03:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, here. You take it.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:39.53,0:03:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You live above the cliffs, don't you?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:42.02,0:03:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet it's really hard finding seashells there.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:44.71,0:03:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:48.25,0:03:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? So you {\i1}can{\i0} talk.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:51.83,0:03:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, want to come with me to somewhere that has even more seashells?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:55.51,0:03:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,'Kay.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:58.29,0:03:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:59.48,0:04:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you put your ear to a seashell, \Nyou can hear the waves.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:05.73,0:04:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you're right!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:08.43,0:04:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,See you again sometime, okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:11.71,0:04:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:12.66,0:04:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's play again!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:31.03,0:04:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:33.03,0:04:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:36.60,0:04:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to the village{,} and trade these for some rice.{villagers are fine, but not the fishermen}
Dialogue: 5,0:04:39.25,0:04:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:42.19,0:04:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you don't talk to the shore folk.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:46.11,0:04:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:57.33,0:04:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:01.33,0:05:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's asking?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:03.17,0:05:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a mushi-shi who's passing through.{Just your friendly neighborhood mushi-shi.}{i approve}
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.76,0:05:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Ginko.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:07.11,0:05:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea {around here }is showing signs of an impending disaster,
Dialogue: 5,0:05:09.95,0:05:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so I thought I should alert the nearby village.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:13.37,0:05:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,An impending disaster?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:22.49,0:05:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No one's here.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:27.31,0:05:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maybe I could take a small break.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:34.07,0:05:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:37.11,0:05:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This one's so pretty.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:40.59,0:05:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if I can hear the waves in this one too.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:49.62,0:05:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:51.05,0:05:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Birds{'} singing?{rip rice}
Dialogue: 5,0:06:01.00,0:06:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I say "impending disaster,"
Dialogue: 5,0:06:02.66,0:06:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm not exactly sure what the disaster will be.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:05.65,0:06:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can assure you that one {\i1}will{\i0} happen—and soon.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:09.85,0:06:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You should tell the other villagers to be prepared for it.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:15.39,0:06:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll protect my own family.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:18.53,0:06:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers can worry about themselves.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:20.35,0:06:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got nothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:26.33,0:06:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:28.59,0:06:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:33.33,0:06:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:34.79,0:06:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem out of it.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:36.85,0:06:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:44.33,0:06:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want me to take you home?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:47.89,0:06:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shima, you sure this girl can talk?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:51.36,0:06:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she's not saying anything.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:53.43,0:06:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She can!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:56.45,0:06:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:57.70,0:06:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going home!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:59.55,0:07:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you ever listen to me?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:04.05,0:07:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And of all people, why would you talk to {\i1}her{\i0}?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:07.33,0:07:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you never to speak to that girl again.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:15.79,0:07:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:16.90,0:07:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Spit it out.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:20.77,0:07:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear the "song of the seashell"?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:30.29,0:07:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's called the song of the seashell, \Nthe song actually comes from a mushi living inside of it.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:36.51,0:07:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called Yadokaridori or Saezurigai, which means "Hermit-Crab Bird" or "Warbling Shell."{respectively}{Yadokaridori: Hermit-Crab Bird \N Saezurigai: Warbling Shell}
Dialogue: 5,0:07:40.99,0:07:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,While they normally spend their time \Neating seaweed and flying over the sea,
Dialogue: 5,0:07:45.99,0:07:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they come ashore when they sense an impending disaster.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:49.27,0:07:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They then hide in seashells \Nand wait for the disaster to pass.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:56.19,0:08:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that faint voice you heard, \Nthey sing, calling their family to safety.{land, where it's safer}
Dialogue: 5,0:08:03.11,0:08:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But when a person puts one of their shells to their ears,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:05.67,0:08:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that person forgets how to speak.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:09.74,0:08:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a cure?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:12.19,0:08:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:13.33,0:08:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as she hears others talk each day, \Nshe'll get her speech back.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:18.21,0:08:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:21.61,0:08:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This only happened because you didn't listen.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:24.27,0:08:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better not do it again, ever.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:27.02,0:08:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that's the long and short of it.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:29.51,0:08:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The bigger issue is the disaster I mentioned.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:32.27,0:08:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll alert the village myself,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:34.56,0:08:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but you guys should be careful too.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:43.15,0:08:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There'll be a disaster at sea?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:46.15,0:08:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:47.93,0:08:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, a tidal wave?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:49.40,0:08:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying there's going to be a big storm?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:51.97,0:08:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. There are records of both of those happening.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:55.06,0:08:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You should all try to prepare yourselves.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:57.59,0:09:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're {\i1}always{\i0} prepared.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:00.73,0:09:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way of knowing what might happen at sea.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:06.07,0:09:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we prepare ourselves in every possible way.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:08.92,0:09:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the warning,
Dialogue: 5,0:09:10.52,0:09:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's nothing else to be done.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:13.27,0:09:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good, then.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:15.07,0:09:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, stay sharp tomorrow too!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:17.54,0:09:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:19.37,0:09:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,950)}He always tells us to stay sharp,
Dialogue: 5,0:09:22.29,0:09:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but all we ever do is tend to the fish cages.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:27.71,0:09:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I'm bored.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:29.85,0:09:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go back to {\i1}diving{\i0} for fish, not farming them.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:32.20,0:09:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind your tongue.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:33.58,0:09:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The chief fisherman had good reason to change things.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:36.69,0:09:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If the fish farm works out, he can make sure we're fed {\i1}and{\i0} safe.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:41.19,0:09:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, this village will never see another tragedy.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:44.75,0:09:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A tragedy?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:47.45,0:09:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it, again?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:49.33,0:09:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... I'd say it's been nearly ten years now.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:52.60,0:09:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the divers from the chief's ship was eaten by a shark.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:57.36,0:10:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't pull her out of the water in time, you see.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:01.27,0:10:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:03.15,0:10:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That was terrible.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:05.81,0:10:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea that day was stained red with her blood.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:08.62,0:10:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Shortly after that happened, the diver's husband quit and stopped fishing with us.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:13.08,0:10:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He and his daughter live by themselves near the cliffs.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:18.51,0:10:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't say I don't understand him, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:21.55,0:10:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The chief pulled up his own wife first, you see.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:26.61,0:10:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know... I would've done the same thing he did.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:31.55,0:10:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:34.11,0:10:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's when the chief had us try fish farming.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:39.15,0:10:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I can understand him as well.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:42.59,0:10:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a painful tragedy for everyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:52.93,0:10:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Dad.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:54.52,0:10:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:56.87,0:11:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So... today on the shore, I saw Mina.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:01.18,0:11:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But then Mina's dad said she's not allowed to talk to me.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:08.17,0:11:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how come.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:12.11,0:11:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:15.70,0:11:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:17.97,0:11:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let that get to you.{it's a "don't let it bother you" kind of thing}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:21.89,0:11:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't do anything wrong.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:27.79,0:11:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I understand.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:32.57,0:11:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:42.41,0:11:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:43.48,0:11:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a shark!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:46.97,0:11:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wife was...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:07.15,0:12:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If only I had been on that boat with her,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:08.90,0:12:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,this wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:11.43,0:12:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakichi, there was nothing anyone could have done.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:18.09,0:12:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Nothing"?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:20.23,0:12:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say so.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:22.37,0:12:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it was my own fault for putting my wife's life in someone else's hands.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:26.65,0:12:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Please get out.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:30.05,0:12:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}From now on, I'll protect my own family.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:05.67,0:13:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even more of them have come ashore.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:10.97,0:13:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In that faint voice, the seashells are crying out...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:15.27,0:13:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}for the sake of their family...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:17.61,0:13:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and themselves.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:45.15,0:13:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That girl's something else.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:47.87,0:13:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She's still so little.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:49.57,0:13:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:52.43,0:13:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been diving in place of her mom all this time.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:57.13,0:13:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help but feel sorry for her.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:11.83,0:14:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:18.39,0:14:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You must never tell anyone else about this.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:21.75,0:14:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if something happens to me,
Dialogue: 5,0:14:24.95,0:14:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with this, you'll be able to get by.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:29.71,0:14:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No one else is going to protect you.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:35.45,0:14:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to protect yourself, first and foremost.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:44.09,0:14:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:47.05,0:14:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:48.63,0:14:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to talk to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:53.59,0:14:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A mushi-shi came to tell us that a disaster at sea will soon happen.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:57.98,0:14:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You two should be careful too.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:02.07,0:15:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the last person I want to hear that from.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:05.77,0:15:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:06.99,0:15:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you have any idea what's going to happen?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:10.65,0:15:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You were always the first to sense when something was wrong with the sea.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:16.57,0:15:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I care.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:18.67,0:15:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakichi, for the last ten years,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:23.08,0:15:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,this village has managed to avoid any other accidents.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:26.78,0:15:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not about to let anyone die on my watch again.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:33.63,0:15:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So could you please come back to the village and help with the fish farm?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:37.79,0:15:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We've finally managed to make the fish farm sustainable.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:43.33,0:15:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, everyone can feed themselves without having to worry.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:47.87,0:15:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you and your little girl keep on fishing alone, you two may run into danger someday.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:53.31,0:15:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that really what you want?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:56.93,0:15:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you for a long time.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:58.83,0:16:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know there's probably someone you blame more than me.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:02.43,0:16:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't go on blaming yourself anymore! You have to stop.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:06.68,0:16:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have something more important to worry about.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:09.93,0:16:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you care about your daughter's future, so please...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:12.91,0:16:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,come back.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:21.57,0:16:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come again.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:23.59,0:16:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, please be careful.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:43.89,0:16:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The singing stopped.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:54.37,0:16:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:55.76,0:16:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just in case, I'll have everyone take refuge on top of the cliffs.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:15.81,0:17:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw something!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:18.15,0:17:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at them...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:19.62,0:17:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So many dead fish.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:21.77,0:17:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:30.31,0:17:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a red tide!{obv. they're all remakes}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:55.03,0:17:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How could this... happen?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:00.99,0:18:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how we run, we can't escape tragedy.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:08.51,0:18:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, there really {\i1}was{\i0}...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:13.48,0:18:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing we could've done.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:22.77,0:18:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing anyone could have done.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:35.65,0:18:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The red tide's finally retreating, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:39.47,0:18:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:41.23,0:18:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess this marks the end of the fish farm.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:44.20,0:18:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, we can dive for some more and start over again.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:47.42,0:18:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:52.44,0:18:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So you still don't have your voice back?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:55.71,0:18:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:57.89,0:19:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be better to let her hear more voices.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:04.99,0:19:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'm off again.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:19.83,0:19:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's strange.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:21.23,0:19:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Although the red tide has receded, they haven't returned to sea yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:27.15,0:19:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Does that mean...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:29.79,0:19:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the disaster isn't over yet?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:35.97,0:19:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:38.75,0:19:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:48.21,0:19:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakichi!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:50.47,0:19:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go diving yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:52.67,0:19:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,After a red tide, shellfish may become poisonous.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:56.43,0:19:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That only happens rarely.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:58.49,0:20:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know that.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:00.74,0:20:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no other choice.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:04.77,0:20:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you should either.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:08.41,0:20:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The omen hasn't yet passed.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:11.81,0:20:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... what are we supposed to do?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:15.57,0:20:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, Sakichi?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:17.16,0:20:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you suggest we all get by until we can live off the sea again?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:27.85,0:20:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Open it.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:36.27,0:20:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina found that pearl.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:38.57,0:20:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can sell it and share the money.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:40.76,0:20:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be a whole lot, but it should be enough.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:43.43,0:20:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But to give us something so precious...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:46.65,0:20:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better than letting someone else die, isn't it?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:49.93,0:20:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But in exchange,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:52.05,0:20:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,please let me and my daughter come back to the village.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:06.95,0:21:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:09.15,0:21:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we will!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:13.67,0:21:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Later on, along nearby shores, the villagers found a few dead seabirds, probably from eating poisonous shellfish.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:22.61,0:21:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, no one from that particular village died.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:48.39,0:21:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mina!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:50.77,0:21:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:52.46,0:21:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Coming!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:56.69,0:21:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you staring at?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:58.08,0:21:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:59.20,0:22:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing.
